headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 28 points and 10 assists, lifting the Detroit Pistons to a 113-110 overtime win over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham scores 28, Pistons beat Hawks 113-110 in OT

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 43 points and 14 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Chicago Bulls 121-106 Monday night in a showdown between two of the Eastern Conference’s top teams headed in opposite directions.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 43 points, 14 rebounds; 76ers thump Bulls 121-106

headlines.description: — Victor Oladipo entered a game for the first time in nearly a year, a loud ovation greeting him as he stepped onto the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oladipo returns, Herro scores 31, Heat top Rockets 123-106

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 27 points and 13 rebounds as the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Portland Trail Blazers by double digits for the second time in three days, 124-81 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Wolves rout Blazers 124-81, extend win streak to 5

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic sees a big difference between the fourth and fifth seeds in the Western Conference playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Jazz 111-103 in possible playoff preview

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Gregg Popovich tied Don Nelson’s NBA record with his 1,335th career victory as a coach in the San Antonio Spurs’ 117-110 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs' Popovich ties Nelson for NBA career wins record

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had his second triple-double in as many nights with 32 points, 15 rebounds and 13 assists, leading the Denver Nuggets to a 131-124 win over the short-handed Golden State Warriors on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets past Warriors 131-124

events.name: New York Knicks at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Julius Randle hit eight 3-pointers and scored 17 of his career-high 46 points in the third quarter as the New York Knicks rallied from a 20-point deficit and beat the Sacramento Kings 131-115 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle nets career-best 46, Knicks rally past Kings 131-115
